
SCSI stands for *Small Computer System Interface*.

Traditional SCSI hardware not used in modern machines anymore. But the *SCSI protocol* is (due to its adaptibility) - for example in → hardware/USB[USB]. Therefore, such devices are found under → Linux/fhs/dev/index[/dev/sdX].

sa:

 `→ Linux/fhs/dev/sdX`

  → hardware/SATA
  
  The shell command `→ Linux/shell/commands/lsscsi`

